    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory allocation issue in nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_init function\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_init` function in the NR PDCP layer was incorrectly allocating memory for the integrity context. Instead of allocating just the 16-byte key buffer required for NIA1/EIA1 processing, it was allocating a full `nas_stream_cipher_t` structure and treating it as if it were just a key buffer. This caused memory corruption when the integrity functions tried to access the key data.\n\nThis fix corrects the memory allocation pattern to match the EIA1 implementation in the core security library, ensuring proper behavior when integrity protection is enabled for SRBs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/nr_pdcp/nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1.c`: Fixed memory allocation in `nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_init`, updated `nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_integrity` to properly use the key buffer, and corrected `nr_pdcp_integrity_nia1_free_integrity` to match the new allocation approach.\n\n"
}